Author: Nathan Bresette [aut, cre], Ai-Ling Lin [aut], Jianlin Cheng [aut]
Maintainer: Nathan Bresette <nathanbresette04@gmail.com>
Description: Supervised multi-omics integration for block-missing ("ragged") data.
    WOVEN learns a shared latent space across V omics modalities using only
    fully-observed anchor subjects, then projects block-missing subjects via
    Nystrom extension without feature-level imputation. Supervision via
    label-augmented cross-covariance (analogous to DIABLO) with optional
    sparse projection matrices (PMD). Designed for comparative effectiveness
    research where intersection-only methods introduce selection bias.
